Q2/- What is JDBC, Write a note on JDBC driver software.

Answer - JDBC stands for Java Database Connectivity.
It is an interface between Java program and database.
A JDBC driver is a small piece of software that allows JDBC to 
connect to different databases.

A JDBC driver makes it possible to do three things--
1. Establish a connection with a data source.
2. Then send queries to the program
3. Update statements to the data source.